  "prompt": "What function does the nose has in the respiratory system?",
  "response": "The nose plays several important functions in the respiratory system:\n\n1. Air filtering\n- Traps dust, dirt, and other particles\n- Contains small hairs (cilia) that filter incoming air\n- Prevents large particles from entering the lungs\n\n2. Temperature regulation\n- Warms incoming air to body temperature\n- Prevents cold air from directly entering the lungs\n- Helps maintain proper respiratory tract conditions\n\n3. Humidity control\n- Adds moisture to inhaled air\n- Humidifies air through mucous membranes\n- Prevents respiratory tract from becoming dry\n\n4. Initial air conditioning\n- Prepares air for deeper respiratory tract passage\n- Adjusts air temperature and humidity\n- Protects sensitive lung tissues\n\n5. Smell and sensory function\n- Contains olfactory receptors\n- Helps detect potential respiratory hazards\n- Contributes to overall respiratory protection\n\n6. Airflow direction and resistance\n- Shapes and directs air into respiratory tract\n- Provides initial resistance to airflow\n- Helps regulate breathing mechanics\n\nThese functions ensure that air entering the lungs is clean, warm, moist, and properly conditioned for optimal respiratory function.",
